XSStrike
Advanced XSS detection and exploitation suite

Web Application
Description
XSStrike is the most advanced XSS detection suite. It has intelligent payload generation, WAF detection & bypass, and a powerful fuzzing engine.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which xsstrike
Install command:

pip install xsstrike
Basic Syntax
xsstrike -u <url>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
xsstrike -u "http://target.com/page?q=test"

Basic XSS scan	Test for XSS	
xsstrike -u "http://target.com/page?q=test" --crawl

Crawl and test	Full site XSS scan	
xsstrike -u "http://target.com/page?q=test" --fuzzer

Fuzzing mode	Find WAF bypass	
xsstrike -u "http://target.com/page?q=test" --blind

Blind XSS test	Test blind XSS	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Find input parameter
2
Run XSStrike basic scan
3
Use --crawl for full coverage
4
Review found vulnerabilities
5
Test payloads manually
Understanding the Output
Shows reflected parameters, working payloads, and confidence levels.

Important Warnings
•
Only test authorized websites
•
XSS can steal user data
•
Report findings responsibly
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
